
<p>
    For the following problems, you will need to use the following conditions:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>
        If the net force acting on an object is in the <emph>same direction</emph>
        as its velocity, the object will <emph>speed up</emph>.
    </li>
    <li>
        If the net force acting on an object is in the <emph>opposite direction</emph>
        as its velocity, the object will <emph>slow down</emph>.
        If the net force remains in this direction, the object will eventually
        <emph>reverse directions</emph>
    </li>
    <li>
        If the net force acting on an object is equal to zero,
        then the object moves at a constant velocity.
    </li>
    <li>
        If the normal force between an object and a surface is equal to zero,
        the object will <emph>lose contact</emph> with that surface.
    </li>
</ul>


