<h4>
    Answers
</h4>

<ol>
    <li>
        <ol type = 'a'>
            <li>
                The block loses contact with the surface of the ramp if
                \( F \sin \phi > m g \cos \theta \)
            </li>
            <li>
                The block speeds up if \( m g \sin \theta > F \cos \phi \).
                If \( \phi > 90^{\circ} \), then \( F \cos \phi \)
                is negative and the condition is definitely met.
            </li>
            <li>
                The block slows down if \( m g \sin \theta < F \cos \phi \)
            </li>
            <li>
                The block moves at a constant speed if \( m g \sin \theta = F \cos \phi \)
            </li>
        </ol>
    </li>
</ol>